Set theory is a branch of mathematics.  You've probably come across it with Venn diagrams.  Like there's a set of all US Presidents, and a set of all US Senators.  A few people will be members of both sets, like Obama, some only members of one or the other.  Most are in neither set.

Although like a lot of math, it's pretty esoteric.  But it shows us in several sciences.  The one I'm most familiar with is with chemistry.  Group theory is a branch of set theory which helps describe the shapes and symmetries of molecules.

